Date: Wed, 18 Sep 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Compuserve Our World, 03 Sep 2002 [translated from Dutch, edited]
<http://ourworld.cs.com/j1braakman/sep02/bsenl42.htm>


A BSE case in Brandwijk
------------------------
A case of BSE has been recorded in a 7-year-old cow on a farm in
Brandwijk (South Holland). This is the 42nd case of BSE in the
Netherlands since 1997, and the 14th case in 2002.

The cow, Tjerkje 254, born on 07 Jan 1995, was sent by the owner to
an emergency-slaughter facility on 20 Aug 2002. On 21 Aug she was
found positive for BSE by the rapid BSE-test. A subsequent laboratory
investigation has confirmed the initial diagnosis on 29 Aug 2002.

No disease symptoms have been observed in any of the other 103
bovines on the farm. Tjerkje 254 was born and reared on the same
farm, in Brandwijk. As customary, an investigation is being performed
into the feeding on the farm, with special attention to the
ingredients fed to the sick cow during her first months of life. All
cows on the farm have been destroyed. In addition, high-risk animals
on other farms, whose origin was the affected farm, are being traced
back and destroyed.

